  "commentary": "With SPX at 6552.87 trading below the 6573 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are currently net buying the dip as they're short gamma below the flip, but the massive +12.8B gamma wall at 6580 will create heavy selling pressure if we rally toward that level. The gex_surge event combined with the -33.5% 5-min GEX change suggests we're seeing rapid options positioning shifts, likely creating choppier price action as dealers adjust hedges around the 6565 (+9.7B) and 6575 (+7.5B) stabilizing walls. Watch for mean reversion behavior with 6500 as the key downside amplification level where dealer buying accelerates, and 6580 as the critical upside resistance where dealer selling intensifies.",
